race.description: Footts Swan Hill Demolition Group Maiden Plate
race.comment: BEST TERMS (7) produced a nice effort on debut in better company last start over 1400m at Pakenham when third, beaten 7 lengths in a fast run race. Drops back a notch here into what looks a winnable race getting to a more suitable trip. MANHATTAN MABS (11) finished third last start at the first run back from a spell over 1600m at Hamilton when she did her best work late, beaten 2.25 lengths. Fitter for that and she should get a nice run midfield. DAD AND DAVE (8) was solid on debut at Echuca over 1400m with scope to improve. He should appreciate rising to 1600m for the top yard. HEART'S EMBRACE (10) stuck on fairly on debut at Horsham over 1400m and will be better for it. Each way. RING THE SHERIFF (4) resumes. If he's fit enough he's good enough to figure.
